---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  title="Now"
  description="What I'm working on right now — a living signal."
  pathname="/now"
>
  <article class="container-prose pt-20 pb-16">
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
      Living document · last updated 2026-05-06
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold mb-4" style="line-height: 1.2;">Now</h1>
    <p class="text-base mb-12" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
      Inspired by <a href="https://nownownow.com/about" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
        >Derek Sivers' /now movement</a
      >. The portfolio is static; this page is not.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">In active measurement</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      <strong>Investigation Thoroughness — STAGE 4 PR1</strong>: warning-only gate on
      composite-tool / discrepancy citation. Measurement window opens 2026-05-11 (D-5 from now).
      The exit criteria for PR2: false-positive rate &lt; 30%, frequency ≥ 10 / 7 days,
      resolution-direction recall coverage ≥ 50%.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Escalation Cognitive Frame Alignment</strong>: SPEC dated 2026-05-03. Baseline (90-
      day "first-reply additional info request rate" on CORE escalations) and post-PR
      measurement queued. Bot confidence target ≥ 90%, additional-info request rate ≤ 20%.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">Reading / thinking about</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
      <li>How to keep a single-author project resilient to context window pressure</li>
      <li>The relationship between pre-tool-use hooks and human discretion</li>
      <li>What makes a permanent fix actually permanent</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">What I'm not doing</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
      Adding tools just to add them. The next phase of sanctuary is removing, not expanding.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
